DataElementConcept.preferredName: Trail Making Test Assessment First Part Last Number Complete
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A neuropsychological test of visual attention and task switching that requires a subject to connect a sequence of 25 consecutive targets. It provides an easy to administer and reliable assessment of attention, sequencing, cognition, visual search, and motor function._The final result of a determination of the value, significance, or extent of._To possess every necessary or normal part or component or step; having come or been brought to a conclusion._Preceding all others in time or space or degree._One of the portions into which something is regarded as divided and which together constitute a whole._Coming after all others in time or space or degree or being the only one remaining._A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification.
